 the AMD\nsimulations using Gogny interactions with different density dependencies of the\nsymmetry energy term. The calculated $a_{sym}/T$ values show a close relation\nto the symmetry energy at the density at the time of the fragment formation.\nFrom this relation the density of the fragmenting source is determined to be\n$\\rho /\\rho_{0} = (0.63 \\pm 0.03 )$. Using this density, the symmetry energy\ncoefficient and the temperature of fragmenting source are determined in a\nself-consistent manner as $a_{sym} = (24.7 \\pm 3.4) MeV$ and $T=(4.9 \\pm 0.2)$\nMeV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 May 2014 13:54:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 14 Sep 2014 05:47:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
